f psychoanalytic ideas.", "VIOLENT BEHAVIOR:Violent behavior is a high-risk event that nurses must monitor and prevent through various interventions, such as communication, psychological care, and behavioral interventions", "VIRGINIA SATIR:Virginia Satir is a family therapist who emphasizes interpersonal communication and teaches family members communication skills to enhance self-esteem and remove obstacles to personal growth", "VISITING HOURS:A scheduled time when family members can visit patients, with nurses ensuring hygiene and safety protocols>", "VISITOR:A **VISITOR** is an individual who may attend group therapy sessions, often referred by a therapist or psychiatrist. In addition to participating in group therapy, a visitor may also undergo biofeedback therapy, which focuses on teaching techniques for symptom control and relaxation. This dual approach highlights the visitor's engagement in therapeutic processes aimed at improving mental and physical well-being through both group interaction and personalized biofeedback methods.", "VISUAL HALLUCINATIONS:"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}